(77, 'Project complexity', 'project-complexity', 'a:4:{s:4:\"desc\";s:260:\"Project Complexity refers to the level of difficulty to deliver the project and considers three dimensions: Technical, Project Economics and Commercial. Click on each dimension below and respond to the questions to create an initial Project Complexity profile.\";s:5:\"lower\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"medium\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"higher\";s:0:\"\";}', '2017-07-06 13:54:51', '2017-09-10 11:43:22', 'risk', 1, 0, '>77', 72),
(78, 'Project environment', 'project-environment', 'a:4:{s:4:\"desc\";s:361:\"Project Environment refers to the level of initial understanding of the project context in which the project will be delivered. Three dimensions of organisational preparedness are considered: Project Governance, Project Technology and Project Location.\nClick on each dimension below and respond to the questions to create an initial Project Environment profile.\";s:5:\"lower\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"medium\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"higher\";s:0:\"\";}', '2017-07-06 13:55:07', '2017-09-10 11:43:22', 'risk', 1, 0, '>78', 73),
(79, 'Project stakeholders', 'project-stakeholders', 'a:4:{s:4:\"desc\";s:427:\"Project Stakeholders refer to the composition of stakeholders (individuals or groups) who have an interest in your project, and/or have a level of influence over the achievement of your project objectives.  Project Stakeholder dimensions are: Stakeholder Profile, Stakeholder Communication, and Stakeholder Engagement. Click on each dimension below and respond to the questions to create an initial Project Stakeholder profile.\";s:5:\"lower\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"medium\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"higher\";s:0:\"\";}', '2017-07-06 13:55:20', '2017-09-10 11:43:22', 'risk', 1, 0, '>79', 74),
(80, 'Technical', 'technical', 'a:4:{s:4:\"desc\";s:243:\"The Technical dimension of any project considers the level of technical familiarity with the project requirements, and the capability and expertise required at the organisational level to ensure that the project can be successfully delivered. \";s:5:\"lower\";s:783:\"The initial Technical profile of your project indicates strong current capability within your organisation to deliver this project. It is likely that you will have most of the expertise, processes, procedures and tools to ensure that you can move into detailed planning and undertake an initial risk assessment. Since the ‘Technical’ dimension of the project appears to be a ‘lower’ risk area, it is advisable that you access lessons learnt from previous similar projects as you move into the planning stage.  Consider that the ‘Technical’ dimension is only one part of assessing overall ‘Project Complexity’. Continue answering the questions on ‘Project Economics’ and ‘Commercial’ dimensions to gain an overall perspective of the complexity of your project.\";s:6:\"medium\";s:968:\"The initial Technical profile of your project indicates only partial  capability of your organisation to deliver and is currently rated at “medium” risk level. It is likely that you will have some of the expertise, tools and templates, to ensure that you can deliver on the project.  It would be most beneficial to draw on others’ expertise, and where possible access “lessons learnt” from others on related projects with a view to reduce the risk level before moving into the planning stage. Conduct ‘desk’ research to collect information on this particular type of project and seek to validate your findings with the experiences of others – both internal and external to the organisation. Consider the ‘Technical’ dimension is only one part in assessing overall ‘Project Complexity’.  Continue answering the questions on ‘Project Economics’ and ‘Commercial’ dimensions to gain an overall perspective of the complexity of your project.\";s:6:\"higher\";s:875:\"The initial Technical profile indicates that the organisation does not currently have the requisite capability to deliver this project effectively. You may need to investigate the tools, templates and procedures currently in place, and suggest reviews to improve processes, procedures, and standards to support your project. Although your score indicates a ‘high’ level of initial risk on the ‘Technical’ dimension, you would be required to introduce the required changes and draw on the expertise of others to seek to move to ‘medium’ or ‘low’ risk before you progress to the planning stage. Consider that the ‘Technical’ dimension is only one part in assessing overall ‘Project Complexity’.  Continue answering the questions on ‘Project Economics’ and ‘Commercial’ dimensions to gain an overall perspective of the complexity of your project.\";}', '2017-07-06 13:57:53', '2017-09-10 11:43:22', 'risk', 1, 77, '>77>80', 75),
(81, 'Project Economics', 'project-economics', 'a:4:{s:4:\"desc\";s:203:\"The Project Economics dimension considers some of the initial business case assumptions that may significantly impact on the financial returns and project benefits realisation in delivery of the project.\";s:5:\"lower\";s:970:\"The initial Project Economics profile of your project indicates that funding, partnerships and resourcing are a relatively low risk area in the context of achieving project objectives. It is likely that the business case has considered the deliverables of the project and secured the appropriate funding to ensure the project can be planned and executed effectively as well realise identified project benefits. If there are any partnerships, they have been secured and resourcing has been sourced appropriately. Since the ‘Project Economics’ aspect of the project appears to be ‘low’ in risk, it is advisable that you consider lessons learnt from previous projects before moving to the planning stage. Consider the ‘Project Economics’ dimension is only one part of assessing overall ‘Project Complexity’. Continue answering the questions on ‘Technical’ and ‘Commercial’ dimensions to gain an overall perspective of the complexity of your project.\";s:6:\"medium\";s:1058:\"The initial Project Economics profile indicates that there are some  issues in the business case that are likely to affect the financial returns and benefits realisation of your project. It is likely that the business case has not received adequate consideration which may lead to issues later if not addressed timeously in the initiation stage. Although there may current be a lack of clarity on funding, partnerships, and/or resourcing, there is sufficient information for you to collate and draw on experts and other resources to lower the ‘Project Economics’ risk. Since the ‘Project Economics’ dimension of the project appears to be of ‘medium’ risk, it is advisable that you revisit the business case and consider lessons learnt from previous projects before moving forward. Consider that the ‘Project Economics’ dimension is only one part of assessing overall ‘Project Complexity’. Continue answering the questions on ‘Technical’ and ‘Commercial’ dimensions to gain an overall perspective of the complexity of your project.\";s:6:\"higher\";s:820:\"The initial Project Economics profile indicates that there is insufficient funding and resourcing to execute the project effectively. Further, it is unlikely that the project will achieve financial returns or realise stated project benefits. You will need to rework or reconsider your business case to carefully assess the feasibility of the project. Although you have scored ‘high’ risk on ‘Project Economics’, you can make changes and draw on the expertise of others to move to ‘medium’ or ‘low’ risk prior to moving into the planning phase. Consider the ‘Project Economics’ dimension is only one part of assessing overall ‘Project Complexity’. Continue answering the questions on ‘Technical’ and ‘Commercial’ dimensions to gain an overall perspective of the complexity of your project.\";}', '2017-07-06 13:58:03', '2017-09-10 11:43:22', 'risk', 1, 77, '>77>81', 76),
(82, 'Commercial', 'commercial', 'a:4:{s:4:\"desc\";s:230:\"The Commercial dimension considers a selection of anticipated market conditions, together with other commercial requirements to secure supply of key resources (i.e. goods, materials and labour) to successfully deliver the project.\";s:5:\"lower\";s:734:\"The initial Commercial profile of your project indicates good clarity around deliverables, and an awareness of procurement and contract management systems required to execute the project effectively. It is likely that contractors and suppliers are in place to execute the project. Since the ‘Commercial’ dimension of the project appears to be ‘low’ risk, it is advisable that you consider lessons learnt from previous projects to move forward to the planning stage. Consider the ‘Commercial’ dimension is only one part of assessing overall ‘Project Complexity’. Continue answering the questions on ‘Technical’ and ‘Project Economics’ dimensions to gain an overall perspective of the complexity of your project.\";s:6:\"medium\";s:962:\"The initial Commercial profile of your project indicates there is some level of clarity on the deliverables and some awareness of procurement and contract management support systems within the organisation. It is likely that you have some contracts in place but you will need to implement contract management processes before moving to the next stage. Since the ‘Commercial’ dimension of the project appears to be of ‘medium’ risk, it is advisable that you ensure availability of procurement systems and processes, and understand current market conditions. Also engage with contractors to access their knowledge, and ascertain general resource availability before moving to the planning stage. Consider the ‘Commercial’ dimension is only one part of assessing overall ‘Project Complexity’. Continue answering the questions on ‘Technical’ and ‘Project Economics’ dimensions to gain an overall perspective of the complexity of your project.\";s:6:\"higher\";s:972:\"The initial Commercial profile of your project indicates a lack of clarity on the procurement and contract management systems within your organisation. It is therefore likely that there are insufficient supplier contracts in place to ensure appropriate resourcing and work requirement specification. Although you have scored ‘high’ risk on the ‘Commercial’ dimension, you need to ensure contract management processes and procedures are in place. To ensure a thorough understanding of deliverables of your project, draw on experts with regard to procurement management systems and processes. Investigate the general availability of contractors and suppliers for this type of project before proceeding any further. The ‘Commercial’ dimension is only one part of assessing overall ‘Project Complexity’. Continue answering the questions on ‘Technical’ and ‘Project Economics’ dimensions to gain an overall perspective of the complexity of your project.\";}', '2017-07-06 13:58:13', '2017-09-10 11:43:22', 'risk', 1, 77, '>77>82', 77),
(83, 'Project Governance', 'project-governance', 'a:4:{s:4:\"desc\";s:264:\"The Project Governance dimension considers the level of regulatory, compliance, and control issues that govern the project. Project governance provides a decision-making assurance framework that should be sufficiently robust to govern and support project delivery.\";s:5:\"lower\";s:886:\"The initial Project Governance profile of your project indicates that your organisation is largely compliant and adheres to regulations around project delivery. Responses suggest that there are appropriate policies and procedures in place to make decisions about the project. It is likely that you are current with all compliance related issues within the organisation, and proceed to the planning stage. Since the ‘Project Governance’ dimension of the project appears to be ‘low’ in risk, it is advisable that you remain current with all regulatory matters of the industry in which your project is situated. The ‘Project Governance’ dimension is only one part of assessing overall ‘Project Environment’. Continue answering the questions on ‘Project Technology’ and ‘Project Location’ dimensions to gain an overall perspective of the environment of your project.\";s:6:\"medium\";s:698:\"The initial Project Governance profile of your project indicates that your organisation is somewhat compliant. It is likely that you will have some decision-making processes in place and that the project objectives are partially aligned to organisational values. It is advised that you draw on others expertise of others within the organisation to ensure appropriate governance is undertaken before moving to the planning stage. The ‘Project Governance’ dimension is only one part of assessing overall ‘Project Environment’. Continue answering the questions on ‘Project Technology’ and ‘Project Location’ dimensions to gain an overall perspective of the environment of your project.\";s:6:\"higher\";s:918:\"The initial Project Governance profile of your project indicates that your organisation does not currently have the necessary governance requirements in place to deliver this project. You may need to investigate the governance structure currently in place, and suggest amendments to improve compliance and governance before moving out of the initiation to the planning stage. Although you have scored ‘high’ risk on Project Governance, you can implement changes to strengthen governance systems. Research equivalent project organisations and seek the knowledge and expertise of others to try to move to a ‘medium’ or ‘low’ risk profile. The ‘Project Governance’ dimension is only one part of assessing overall ‘Project Environment’. Continue answering the questions on ‘Project Technology’ and ‘Project Location’ dimensions to gain an overall perspective of the environment of your project.\";}', '2017-07-06 13:58:40', '2017-09-10 11:43:22', 'risk', 1, 78, '>78>83', 78),
(84, 'Project Technology', 'project-technology', 'a:4:{s:4:\"desc\";s:160:\"The Project Technology dimension refers to the level of technology, or technological infrastructure complexity that is required for successful project delivery.\";s:5:\"lower\";s:820:\"The initial Project Technology profile indicates that you have sound understanding of the key technology requirements of the project. Additionally, the organisation has sufficient resources, and capability to integrate the requisite technology in the project. Since the ‘Project Technology’ dimension of the project appears to be ‘low’ in risk, it is advisable that you keep up-to-date with technological trends and possible changes in technology between initiation/planning and execution stages to ensure that the capability remains current. The ‘Project Technology’ dimension is only one part of assessing overall ‘Project Environment’. Continue answering the questions on ‘Project Governance’ and ‘Project Location’ dimensions to gain an overall perspective of the environment of your project.\";s:6:\"medium\";s:779:\"The initial Project Technology profile indicates that there are some areas where there is uncertainty about the use and integration of technology in your project. Although there is current lack of clarity on technology, there is sufficient information for you to collate or source and integrate appropriate technology. Since the ‘Project Technology’ dimension appears to be of ‘medium’ risk, it is advisable that you draw on technology experts that can guide you before moving into the planning phase. The ‘Project Technology’ dimension is only one part of assessing overall ‘Project Environment’. Continue answering the questions on ‘Project Governance’ and ‘Project Location’ dimensions to gain an overall perspective of the environment of your project.\";s:6:\"higher\";s:894:\"The initial Project Technology profile indicates that there is insufficient knowledge around the technology required for the project. You will need to rethink your approach to using a particular technology, or outsource the appropriate technology and skills to move the project forward. Although you have scored ‘high’ risk on ‘Project Technology’, you can allocate resources, new technology and draw on the expertise of others to move to ‘medium’ or ‘low’ risk. Do not move out of the initiation stage to the planning stage until you have a greater degree of clarity around the technology requirements. The ‘Project Technology’ dimension is only one dimension of assessing overall ‘Project Environment’. Continue answering the questions on ‘Project Governance’ and ‘Project Location’ dimensions to gain an overall perspective of the environment of your project.\";}', '2017-07-06 14:01:37', '2017-09-10 11:43:22', 'risk', 1, 78, '>78>84', 79),
(85, 'Project Location', 'project-location', 'a:4:{s:4:\"desc\";s:221:\"The Project Location dimension considers the geographical location and climatic conditions of the project delivery site, and the level of familiarity with the expected conditions under which the project will be delivered.\";s:5:\"lower\";s:659:\"The initial Project Location profile indicates that you have sufficient knowledge of the location. You appear to be are aware of any local requirements pertaining to the location. Since the ‘Project Location’ dimension of the project appears to be ‘low’ in risk, it is advisable that you consider lessons learnt from previous projects as you move forward to the planning stage. The ‘Project Location’ dimension is only one part of assessing overall ‘Project Environment’. Continue responding to the questions on ‘Project Governance’ and ‘Project Technology’ dimensions to gain an overall perspective of the environment of your project.\";s:6:\"medium\";s:885:\"The initial Project Location profile indicates that you have some clarity regarding project location issues and partial awareness of the requirements in that location. It is likely that you have some knowledge of the location and that you may need to relocate stakeholders to deliver the project. Since the ‘Project Location’ dimension of the project appears to be of ‘medium’ risk, it is advisable that you further research and develop a full understanding of location requirements, climatic conditions as well as any local customs that may impact on project delivery before moving into the planning stage. The ‘Project Location’ dimension is only one part of assessing overall ‘Project Environment’. Continue answering the questions on ‘Project Governance’ and ‘Project Technology’ dimensions to gain an overall perspective of the environment of your project.\";s:6:\"higher\";s:975:\"The initial Project Location profile indicates that you currently have a lack of clarity regarding the project environment, location, and customs. Most likely this is a location you have never delivered a project previously, and need to obtain further clarity regarding skilled resource availability close to the location, otherwise these will need to be moved to the location. Although you have scored ‘high’ risk on ‘Project Location’ dimension, you can improve your understanding of location conditions, by visiting the location, and drawing on local experts, having discussions with locals, contractors and suppliers situated at or near the location, before moving out of the initiation stage. The ‘Project Location’ dimension is only one part of assessing overall ‘Project Environment’. Continue answering the questions on ‘Project Governance’ and ‘Project Technology’ dimensions to gain an overall perspective of the environment of your project.\";}', '2017-07-06 14:01:53', '2017-09-10 11:43:22', 'risk', 1, 78, '>78>85', 80),
(86, 'Stakeholder Profiles', 'stakeholder-profiles', 'a:4:{s:4:\"desc\";s:383:\"The Stakeholder Profile dimension considers how stakeholders are classified. Stakeholders are classified as internal or external to your project. Internal stakeholders are considered as within the project organisation. External stakeholders are outside the project organisation. Stakeholder classification will inform the level of stakeholder management involved in project delivery.\";s:5:\"lower\";s:752:\"The initial Project Stakeholder profile indicates that you anticipate your stakeholders to be relatively well aligned with the objectives of your project.  Since the ‘profile’ of stakeholders appears to be ‘low’, it is likely that you are anticipating less time and resources to be applied to maintaining good alignment through the project phases. Reflect on lessons learnt from similar projects in similar locations before proceeding to the planning stage.  The ‘Stakeholder Profile’ dimension is only one part in assessing overall ‘Project Stakeholders’. Continue answering the questions on ‘Stakeholder Communication’ and ‘Stakeholder Engagement’ dimensions to gain an overall perspective of the stakeholders of your project.\";s:6:\"medium\";s:827:\"The initial Project Stakeholder profile indicates that you anticipate your stakeholders to be moderately aligned with the objectives of your project.  Since the ‘profile’ of stakeholders appears to be ‘medium’, it is likely that you may experience some misalignment from your internal and external stakeholders over some of the key issues.  Before moving out of the initiation phase you need to determine whether there are significant areas of possible conflict, and a strategy to address these before you move to the planning stage. The ‘Stakeholder Profile’ dimension is only one part in assessing overall ‘Project Stakeholders’. Continue answering the questions on ‘Stakeholder Communication’ and ‘Stakeholder Engagement’ dimensions to gain an overall perspective of the stakeholders of your project.\";s:6:\"higher\";s:737:\"The initial Project Stakeholder profile indicates that you anticipate your stakeholders to be only marginally aligned with the objectives of your project.  Since the ‘profile’ of stakeholders appears to be ‘high’, it is likely that you may experience greater levels of uncertainty and objection from your stakeholders. Ensure that you understand the differences and how these will be managed and harmonised before moving to the planning stage. The ‘Stakeholder Profile’ dimension is only one part in assessing overall ‘Project Stakeholders’. Continue answering the questions on ‘Stakeholder Communication’ and ‘Stakeholder Engagement’ dimensions to gain an overall perspective of the stakeholders of your project.\";}', '2017-07-06 14:02:17', '2017-09-10 11:43:22', 'risk', 1, 79, '>79>86', 81),
(87, 'Stakeholder Communication', 'stakeholder-communication', 'a:4:{s:4:\"desc\";s:290:\"The Stakeholder Communication dimension is concerned with the level and frequency of communication required with internal and external stakeholders. Developing appropriate and effective communication strategies is essential to ensure stakeholders remain aligned to achieve project outcomes.\";s:5:\"lower\";s:715:\"The initial Stakeholder Communication profile indicates that you may have effective communication strategies in place to communicate with your internal and external stakeholders. Since the ‘Communications’ aspect is ‘low’ risk, you may want to monitor the strategy that is in place to ensure that there is continuous effective communication with both internal and external stakeholders throughout the project life cycle. The ‘Stakeholder Communication’ dimension is only one part of assessing overall ‘Project Stakeholders’. Continue answering the questions on ‘Stakeholder Profiles’ and ‘Stakeholder Engagement’ dimensions to gain an overall perspective of the stakeholders of your project.\";s:6:\"medium\";s:798:\"The initial Stakeholder Communication profile indicates that you may need to adapt your communication strategy. Effective communication with the different stakeholder groups require the development of a robust and integrated communication strategy. Since the ‘Stakeholder Communication’ aspect of the project appears to be of ‘medium’ risk, it is advisable that you reconsider your communication strategies with each key stakeholder group, considering lessons learnt before moving to the planning stage. The ‘Stakeholder Communication’ dimension is only one part of assessing overall ‘Project Stakeholders’. Continue answering the questions on ‘Stakeholder Profiles’ and ‘Stakeholder Engagement’ dimensions to gain an overall perspective of the stakeholders of your project.\";s:6:\"higher\";s:677:\"The initial Stakeholder Communication profile indicates that the   current communication strategy is either an insufficient or ineffective to communicate with your stakeholders. You will need to develop a new integrated communication strategy, or reconsider your current strategy to ensure that you can regularly communicate with your stakeholders before moving out of the initiation stage. The ‘Stakeholder Communication’ dimension is only one part of assessing overall ‘Project Stakeholders’. Continue answering the questions on ‘Stakeholder Profiles’ and ‘Stakeholder Engagement’ dimensions to gain an overall perspective of the stakeholders of your project.\";}', '2017-07-06 14:02:27', '2017-09-10 11:43:22', 'risk', 1, 79, '>79>87', 82),
(88, 'Stakeholder Engagement', 'stakeholder-engagement', 'a:4:{s:4:\"desc\";s:307:\"The Stakeholder Engagement dimension refers to the level of interest, and level of influence that your stakeholders may have on achieving your project objectives, and your ability to pro-actively plan and manage the engagement. Dynamic stakeholder engagement is key to ensure project outcomes are delivered.\";s:5:\"lower\";s:753:\"The initial Stakeholder Engagement profile indicates that your stakeholders are interested in, and have impact on the project outcomes. Further, it appears that internal and external stakeholders support the project rather than pose challenges to project delivery. Since the ‘Stakeholder Engagement’ aspect of the project appears to be ‘low’ in risk, it is advisable that you consider lessons learnt from previous projects before moving to the planning stage. The ‘Stakeholder Engagement’ dimension is only one part of assessing overall ‘Project Stakeholders’. Continue answering the questions on ‘Stakeholder Profiles’ and ‘Stakeholder Communication’ dimensions to gain an overall perspective of the environment of your project.\";s:6:\"medium\";s:982:\"The initial Stakeholder Engagement profile indicates that you may experience varying levels of engagement and some uncertainty from your stakeholders. It is likely that you have some idea about how the stakeholders are likely to respond to the project. You will need to be clear on their level of interest and their ability to adversely influence project outcomes and ensure responsive strategies to pro-actively manage resistance from both internal and external stakeholders. Since the ‘Stakeholder Engagement’ aspect of the project stakeholders appears to be of ‘medium’, it is advisable that you meet with stakeholders to secure their input and support before moving to planning stage. The ‘Stakeholder Engagement’ dimension is only one part of assessing overall ‘Project Stakeholders’. Continue answering the questions on ‘Stakeholder Profiles’ and ‘Stakeholder Communication’ dimensions to gain an overall perspective of the environment of your project.\";s:6:\"higher\";s:867:\"The initial Stakeholder Engagement profile indicates that you may experience varying levels of engagement from your stakeholders. Stakeholders who agitate and have influence over project outcomes are a threat to your project. If either internal or external stakeholders pose significant challenges to project delivery, you will not be able to move forward until you have gained a complete understanding of their motivations.  To do this, you need to draw on experts and engage with key project stakeholders to ascertain their level of interest and influence over project outcomes.  The ‘Stakeholder Engagement’ dimension is only one part of assessing overall ‘Project Stakeholders’. Continue answering the questions on ‘Stakeholder Profiles’ and ‘Stakeholder Communication’ dimensions to gain an overall perspective of the environment of your project.\";}', '2017-07-06 14:02:47', '2017-09-10 11:43:22', 'risk', 1, 79, '>79>88', 83),
